[Experiment] **Hybrid scheduled WD: linear (0.1→0.06) until 60%, then constant 0.02 + exponential warmup + cosine LR + EMA + beta2=0.99**

Combine smooth scheduled decay in the first phase with a sharp drop for the second phase. Linear decay 0.1→0.06 during main learning prevents gradual overfitting, then sharp drop to 0.02 at 60% enables aggressive final fitting. This hybrid approach may capture benefits of both smooth and two-phase schedules.

